; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  talked the other day</a> about the me=
chanics of Silicon Valley Bank=E2=80=99s failure. Those mechanics are that =
a lot of depositors asked for their money back one Thursday, and SVB didn=
=E2=80=99t have enough money to give them: It ended the day with negative m=
oney, and was shut down by its regulators. This is a somewhat weird thing t=
o happen in a modern banking system: Silicon Valley Bank had lots of valuab=
le, safe, liquid=C2=A0<em>assets</em>, and it is a US bank with access to t=
he Federal Reserve. It seems like it should have been fairly straightforwar=
d for SVB to pledge those assets to the Federal Reserve to borrow enough mo=
ney to meet its deposit outflows.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And in fact SVB tried to do that, and it appar=
ently did have enough collateral to borrow enough money to pay out its depo=
sitors that Thursday, though I=E2=80=99m not sure it would have survived th=
e weekend. But the problem, that Thursday, was not that SVB had insufficien=
t assets; the problem was that the Fed=E2=80=99s computer systems stopped w=
orking at 4 p.m. California time, and SVB missed the cutoff to transfer ass=
ets and borrow money. Silicon Valley Bank certainly had financial problems =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0the Federal Deposit Insurance Corp. finally <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30986595.262435/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYm=
xvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMjcvdGhlLWNmdGMtY29tZXMtZ=
m9yLWJpbmFuY2U_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMyODIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1=
dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMzI4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN=
0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb7a2f4c8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  sold it off yesterday<=
/a> for something like negative $20 billion!<a class=3D"footnote-index" hre=
f=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inl=
ine-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0=E2=80=94 but the reason it failed=C2=A0<em>that day=C2=A0</em>wa=
s mostly operational, not financial.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Today the US Senate is <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30986595.262435/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmFua2luZ=
